Package: neighborhood
Type: Package
Title: Neighborhood analysis functions
Version: 1.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Tim",
           family = "Thomas",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "timthomas@berkeley.edu"),
    person(given = "Alex",
           family = "Ramiller",
           role = c("ctb"))
    )
Description: This package features several neighborhood research functions in
    relation to racial segregation, housing market trends, and residential
    mobility. It also provides a small, customizable toolkit for building
    interactive MapLibre GL maps of census-tract data (legends, labels, popups,
    and PMTiles vector tiles), built on the 'mapgl' and 'tidycensus' packages by
    Kyle Walker. Mapping functions are deterministic and require no AI to run.
